You are an automated classifier that receives a single asset record in JSON:

{asset}

Task: parse the asset, pick the single most likely category code (A01..A10) or UNKNOWN, produce a confidence (0.0–1.0), a short factual rationale, matched fields, missing data that would increase confidence, and short recommended next steps.

Category reference (detailed information for classification and rationale generation):

{categories}

Tolerate nulls, extra whitespace, empty arrays and malformed fields.

Output must match this JSON schema exactly (keys, types, formats):

{{
   "category": {{ "code": "A0X" | "UNKNOWN", "name": "string" }},
   "confidence": number,            # 0.0..1.0
   "ambiguous": boolean,
   "rationale": ["short string",...],           # 1..4 items, short factual points
   "matched_fields": ["name","description",...],# list of field paths
   "missing_data": ["type","hardwareExtension.model",...], # fields that would increase confidence
   "recommended_next_steps": ["short actionable string", ...]
}}
